{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":680,"text":"Imagine you're walking through a forest."},{"time":3960,"text":"I'm guessing you're thinking\nof a collection of trees,"},{"time":7120,"text":"what we foresters call a stand,"},{"time":9880,"text":"with their rugged stems\nand their beautiful crowns."},{"time":13360,"text":"Yes, trees are the foundation of forests,"},{"time":16480,"text":"but a forest is much more\nthan what you see,"},{"time":19560,"text":"and today I want to change\nthe way you think about forests."},{"time":23880,"text":"You see, underground\nthere is this other world,"},{"time":27280,"text":"a world of infinite biological pathways"},{"time":30360,"text":"that connect trees\nand allow them to communicate"},{"time":33800,"text":"and allow the forest to behave\nas though it's a single organism."},{"time":38040,"text":"It might remind you\nof a sort of intelligence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":41600,"text":"How do I know this?"},{"time":43280,"text":"Here's my story."},{"time":45560,"text":"I grew up in the forests\nof British Columbia."},{"time":49080,"text":"I used to lay on the forest floor\nand stare up at the tree crowns."},{"time":52280,"text":"They were giants."},{"time":54320,"text":"My grandfather was a giant, too."},{"time":55920,"text":"He was a horse logger,"},{"time":57400,"text":"and he used to selectively cut\ncedar poles from the inland rainforest."},{"time":61760,"text":"Grandpa taught me about the quiet\nand cohesive ways of the woods,"},{"time":65760,"text":"and how my family was knit into it."},{"time":69080,"text":"So I followed in grandpa's footsteps."}]},{"cues":[{"time":71240,"text":"He and I had this curiosity about forests,"},{"time":74800,"text":"and my first big \"aha\" moment"},{"time":76960,"text":"was at the outhouse by our lake."},{"time":79640,"text":"Our poor dog Jigs\nhad slipped and fallen into the pit."},{"time":84080,"text":"So grandpa ran up with his shovel\nto rescue the poor dog."},{"time":87240,"text":"He was down there, swimming in the muck."},{"time":91000,"text":"But as grandpa dug\nthrough that forest floor,"},{"time":93720,"text":"I became fascinated with the roots,"},{"time":96360,"text":"and under that, what I learned later\nwas the white mycelium"},{"time":99480,"text":"and under that the red\nand yellow mineral horizons."},{"time":103240,"text":"Eventually, grandpa and I\nrescued the poor dog,"},{"time":106440,"text":"but it was at that moment that I realized"},{"time":108800,"text":"that that palette of roots and soil"},{"time":111400,"text":"was really the foundation of the forest."}]},{"cues":[{"time":114640,"text":"And I wanted to know more."},{"time":116680,"text":"So I studied forestry."},{"time":119440,"text":"But soon I found myself working\nalongside the powerful people"},{"time":123080,"text":"in charge of the commercial harvest."},{"time":125960,"text":"The extent of the clear-cutting"},{"time":128560,"text":"was alarming,"},{"time":129840,"text":"and I soon found myself\nconflicted by my part in it."},{"time":133600,"text":"Not only that, the spraying\nand hacking of the aspens and birches"},{"time":138720,"text":"to make way for the more commercially\nvaluable planted pines and firs"},{"time":143040,"text":"was astounding."},{"time":145040,"text":"It seemed that nothing could stop\nthis relentless industrial machine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":149640,"text":"So I went back to school,"},{"time":152360,"text":"and I studied my other world."},{"time":155480,"text":"You see, scientists had just discovered\nin the laboratory in vitro"},{"time":159760,"text":"that one pine seedling root"},{"time":161920,"text":"could transmit carbon\nto another pine seedling root."},{"time":166160,"text":"But this was in the laboratory,"},{"time":167960,"text":"and I wondered,\ncould this happen in real forests?"},{"time":171040,"text":"I thought yes."},{"time":173120,"text":"Trees in real forests might also\nshare information below ground."},{"time":178120,"text":"But this was really controversial,"},{"time":179920,"text":"and some people thought I was crazy,"},{"time":182560,"text":"and I had a really hard time\ngetting research funding."},{"time":185640,"text":"But I persevered,"},{"time":188200,"text":"and I eventually conducted\nsome experiments deep in the forest,"},{"time":192080,"text":"25 years ago."},{"time":194120,"text":"I grew 80 replicates of three species:"},{"time":197040,"text":"paper birch, Douglas fir,\nand western red cedar."},{"time":200240,"text":"I figured the birch and the fir\nwould be connected in a belowground web,"},{"time":204320,"text":"but not the cedar."},{"time":205600,"text":"It was in its own other world."},{"time":208440,"text":"And I gathered my apparatus,"},{"time":210320,"text":"and I had no money,\nso I had to do it on the cheap."},{"time":213520,"text":"So I went to Canadian Tire --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":215160,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":216600,"text":"and I bought some plastic bags\nand duct tape and shade cloth,"},{"time":220040,"text":"a timer, a paper suit, a respirator."},{"time":224160,"text":"And then I borrowed some\nhigh-tech stuff from my university:"},{"time":227360,"text":"a Geiger counter, a scintillation counter,\na mass spectrometer, microscopes."},{"time":232000,"text":"And then I got some\nreally dangerous stuff:"},{"time":234480,"text":"syringes full of radioactive\ncarbon-14 carbon dioxide gas"},{"time":239280,"text":"and some high pressure bottles"},{"time":241320,"text":"of the stable isotope\ncarbon-13 carbon dioxide gas."},{"time":245560,"text":"But I was legally permitted."}]},{"cues":[{"time":247160,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":248880,"text":"Oh, and I forgot some stuff,"},{"time":251080,"text":"important stuff: the bug spray,"},{"time":253600,"text":"the bear spray,\nthe filters for my respirator."},{"time":257160,"text":"Oh well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":259560,"text":"The first day of the experiment,\nwe got out to our plot"},{"time":262360,"text":"and a grizzly bear and her cub\nchased us off."},{"time":265920,"text":"And I had no bear spray."},{"time":269120,"text":"But you know, this is how\nforest research in Canada goes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":272320,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":273800,"text":"So I came back the next day,"},{"time":275360,"text":"and mama grizzly and her cub were gone."},{"time":277640,"text":"So this time, we really got started,"},{"time":279680,"text":"and I pulled on my white paper suit,"},{"time":282480,"text":"I put on my respirator,"},{"time":286160,"text":"and then"},{"time":287400,"text":"I put the plastic bags over my trees."},{"time":291080,"text":"I got my giant syringes,"},{"time":293200,"text":"and I injected the bags"},{"time":294880,"text":"with my tracer isotope\ncarbon dioxide gases,"},{"time":298320,"text":"first the birch."},{"time":299560,"text":"I injected carbon-14, the radioactive gas,"},{"time":302560,"text":"into the bag of birch."},{"time":304160,"text":"And then for fir,"},{"time":305440,"text":"I injected the stable isotope\ncarbon-13 carbon dioxide gas."},{"time":309280,"text":"I used two isotopes,"},{"time":311040,"text":"because I was wondering"},{"time":312320,"text":"whether there was two-way communication\ngoing on between these species."},{"time":317640,"text":"I got to the final bag,"},{"time":320240,"text":"the 80th replicate,"},{"time":321760,"text":"and all of a sudden\nmama grizzly showed up again."},{"time":324200,"text":"And she started to chase me,"},{"time":325640,"text":"and I had my syringes above my head,"},{"time":328080,"text":"and I was swatting the mosquitos,\nand I jumped into the truck,"},{"time":331040,"text":"and I thought,"},{"time":332280,"text":"\"This is why people do lab studies.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":334040,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":337120,"text":"I waited an hour."},{"time":338640,"text":"I figured it would take this long"},{"time":340280,"text":"for the trees to suck up\nthe CO2 through photosynthesis,"},{"time":343080,"text":"turn it into sugars,\nsend it down into their roots,"},{"time":346240,"text":"and maybe, I hypothesized,"},{"time":348960,"text":"shuttle that carbon belowground\nto their neighbors."},{"time":352920,"text":"After the hour was up,"},{"time":354800,"text":"I rolled down my window,"},{"time":356400,"text":"and I checked for mama grizzly."},{"time":358600,"text":"Oh good, she's over there\neating her huckleberries."},{"time":361720,"text":"So I got out of the truck\nand I got to work."},{"time":364360,"text":"I went to my first bag with the birch.\nI pulled the bag off."},{"time":368280,"text":"I ran my Geiger counter over its leaves."},{"time":371280,"text":"Kkhh!"},{"time":373400,"text":"Perfect."},{"time":374640,"text":"The birch had taken up\nthe radioactive gas."},{"time":377600,"text":"Then the moment of truth."},{"time":379200,"text":"I went over to the fir tree."},{"time":381320,"text":"I pulled off its bag."},{"time":383120,"text":"I ran the Geiger counter up its needles,"},{"time":385480,"text":"and I heard the most beautiful sound."},{"time":388440,"text":"Kkhh!"},{"time":390760,"text":"It was the sound of birch talking to fir,"},{"time":393520,"text":"and birch was saying,\n\"Hey, can I help you?\""},{"time":397000,"text":"And fir was saying, \"Yeah,\ncan you send me some of your carbon?"},{"time":400640,"text":"Because somebody\nthrew a shade cloth over me.\""},{"time":404360,"text":"I went up to cedar, and I ran\nthe Geiger counter over its leaves,"},{"time":408080,"text":"and as I suspected,"},{"time":410520,"text":"silence."},{"time":412560,"text":"Cedar was in its own world."},{"time":414800,"text":"It was not connected into the web\ninterlinking birch and fir."}]},{"cues":[{"time":419840,"text":"I was so excited,"},{"time":422000,"text":"I ran from plot to plot\nand I checked all 80 replicates."},{"time":426000,"text":"The evidence was clear."},{"time":428160,"text":"The C-13 and C-14 was showing me"},{"time":431120,"text":"that paper birch and Douglas fir\nwere in a lively two-way conversation."},{"time":435960,"text":"It turns out at that time of the year,"},{"time":437840,"text":"in the summer,"},{"time":439080,"text":"that birch was sending more carbon to fir\nthan fir was sending back to birch,"},{"time":442760,"text":"especially when the fir was shaded."},{"time":445080,"text":"And then in later experiments,\nwe found the opposite,"},{"time":448080,"text":"that fir was sending more carbon to birch\nthan birch was sending to fir,"},{"time":451640,"text":"and this was because the fir was still\ngrowing while the birch was leafless."},{"time":455880,"text":"So it turns out the two species\nwere interdependent,"},{"time":458560,"text":"like yin and yang."}]},{"cues":[{"time":460960,"text":"And at that moment,\neverything came into focus for me."},{"time":463960,"text":"I knew I had found something big,"},{"time":466240,"text":"something that would change the way\nwe look at how trees interact in forests,"},{"time":471000,"text":"from not just competitors"},{"time":473040,"text":"but to cooperators."},{"time":475800,"text":"And I had found solid evidence"},{"time":478280,"text":"of this massive belowground\ncommunications network,"},{"time":481680,"text":"the other world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":483960,"text":"Now, I truly hoped and believed"},{"time":485880,"text":"that my discovery would change\nhow we practice forestry,"},{"time":489520,"text":"from clear-cutting and herbiciding"},{"time":491320,"text":"to more holistic and sustainable methods,"},{"time":494280,"text":"methods that were less expensive\nand more practical."},{"time":497520,"text":"What was I thinking?"},{"time":499920,"text":"I'll come back to that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":503760,"text":"So how do we do science\nin complex systems like forests?"},{"time":508720,"text":"Well, as forest scientists,\nwe have to do our research in the forests,"},{"time":512080,"text":"and that's really tough,\nas I've shown you."},{"time":514120,"text":"And we have to be really good\nat running from bears."},{"time":518760,"text":"But mostly, we have to persevere"},{"time":520360,"text":"in spite of all the stuff\nstacked against us."},{"time":523280,"text":"And we have to follow our intuition\nand our experiences"},{"time":525920,"text":"and ask really good questions."},{"time":528080,"text":"And then we've got to gather our data\nand then go verify."},{"time":531280,"text":"For me, I've conducted and published\nhundreds of experiments in the forest."},{"time":537080,"text":"Some of my oldest experimental plantations\nare now over 30 years old."},{"time":542040,"text":"You can check them out."},{"time":543480,"text":"That's how forest science works."}]},{"cues":[{"time":546200,"text":"So now I want to talk about the science."},{"time":548560,"text":"How were paper birch\nand Douglas fir communicating?"},{"time":551640,"text":"Well, it turns out they were conversing\nnot only in the language of carbon"},{"time":556160,"text":"but also nitrogen and phosphorus"},{"time":559200,"text":"and water and defense signals\nand allele chemicals and hormones --"},{"time":563960,"text":"information."},{"time":566160,"text":"And you know, I have to tell you,\nbefore me, scientists had thought"},{"time":569360,"text":"that this belowground\nmutualistic symbiosis called a mycorrhiza"},{"time":572960,"text":"was involved."},{"time":574480,"text":"Mycorrhiza literally means \"fungus root.\""},{"time":578360,"text":"You see their reproductive organs\nwhen you walk through the forest."},{"time":582280,"text":"They're the mushrooms."},{"time":584120,"text":"The mushrooms, though,\nare just the tip of the iceberg,"},{"time":587160,"text":"because coming out of those stems\nare fungal threads that form a mycelium,"},{"time":591440,"text":"and that mycelium\ninfects and colonizes the roots"},{"time":594160,"text":"of all the trees and plants."},{"time":596320,"text":"And where the fungal cells\ninteract with the root cells,"},{"time":599000,"text":"there's a trade of carbon for nutrients,"},{"time":601800,"text":"and that fungus gets those nutrients\nby growing through the soil"},{"time":604880,"text":"and coating every soil particle."},{"time":607840,"text":"The web is so dense that there can be\nhundreds of kilometers of mycelium"},{"time":612160,"text":"under a single footstep."},{"time":614720,"text":"And not only that, that mycelium connects\ndifferent individuals in the forest,"},{"time":620320,"text":"individuals not only of the same species\nbut between species, like birch and fir,"},{"time":625960,"text":"and it works kind of like the Internet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":629760,"text":"You see, like all networks,"},{"time":631680,"text":"mycorrhizal networks have nodes and links."},{"time":634520,"text":"We made this map by examining\nthe short sequences of DNA"},{"time":638600,"text":"of every tree and every fungal individual\nin a patch of Douglas fir forest."},{"time":644120,"text":"In this picture, the circles represent\nthe Douglas fir, or the nodes,"},{"time":647960,"text":"and the lines represent the interlinking\nfungal highways, or the links."}]},{"cues":[{"time":653120,"text":"The biggest, darkest nodes\nare the busiest nodes."},{"time":657480,"text":"We call those hub trees,"},{"time":659440,"text":"or more fondly, mother trees,"},{"time":661880,"text":"because it turns out\nthat those hub trees nurture their young,"},{"time":666520,"text":"the ones growing in the understory."},{"time":669080,"text":"And if you can see those yellow dots,"},{"time":671240,"text":"those are the young seedlings\nthat have established within the network"},{"time":674560,"text":"of the old mother trees."},{"time":676400,"text":"In a single forest, a mother tree can be\nconnected to hundreds of other trees."},{"time":681800,"text":"And using our isotope tracers,"},{"time":684120,"text":"we have found that mother trees"},{"time":685640,"text":"will send their excess carbon\nthrough the mycorrhizal network"},{"time":688600,"text":"to the understory seedlings,"},{"time":690560,"text":"and we've associated this\nwith increased seedling survival"},{"time":693720,"text":"by four times."}]},{"cues":[{"time":695880,"text":"Now, we know we all\nfavor our own children,"},{"time":699120,"text":"and I wondered, could Douglas fir\nrecognize its own kin,"},{"time":703760,"text":"like mama grizzly and her cub?"},{"time":706560,"text":"So we set about an experiment,"},{"time":708400,"text":"and we grew mother trees\nwith kin and stranger's seedlings."},{"time":712320,"text":"And it turns out\nthey do recognize their kin."},{"time":715240,"text":"Mother trees colonize their kin\nwith bigger mycorrhizal networks."},{"time":720240,"text":"They send them more carbon below ground."},{"time":722680,"text":"They even reduce\ntheir own root competition"},{"time":725280,"text":"to make elbow room for their kids."},{"time":728160,"text":"When mother trees are injured or dying,"},{"time":731840,"text":"they also send messages of wisdom\non to the next generation of seedlings."},{"time":737120,"text":"So we've used isotope tracing"},{"time":738680,"text":"to trace carbon moving\nfrom an injured mother tree"},{"time":741280,"text":"down her trunk\ninto the mycorrhizal network"},{"time":743640,"text":"and into her neighboring seedlings,"},{"time":746640,"text":"not only carbon but also defense signals."},{"time":749440,"text":"And these two compounds"},{"time":751280,"text":"have increased the resistance\nof those seedlings to future stresses."},{"time":755400,"text":"So trees talk."}]},{"cues":[{"time":758560,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":760600,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":765440,"text":"Through back and forth conversations,"},{"time":767760,"text":"they increase the resilience\nof the whole community."},{"time":771360,"text":"It probably reminds you\nof our own social communities,"},{"time":774280,"text":"and our families,"},{"time":775880,"text":"well, at least some families."}]},{"cues":[{"time":777285,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":779520,"text":"So let's come back to the initial point."},{"time":782480,"text":"Forests aren't simply\ncollections of trees,"},{"time":784960,"text":"they're complex systems\nwith hubs and networks"},{"time":788520,"text":"that overlap and connect trees\nand allow them to communicate,"},{"time":792040,"text":"and they provide avenues\nfor feedbacks and adaptation,"},{"time":795840,"text":"and this makes the forest resilient."},{"time":798280,"text":"That's because there are many hub trees\nand many overlapping networks."},{"time":802680,"text":"But they're also vulnerable,"},{"time":804680,"text":"vulnerable not only\nto natural disturbances"},{"time":808200,"text":"like bark beetles that preferentially\nattack big old trees"},{"time":811920,"text":"but high-grade logging\nand clear-cut logging."},{"time":815240,"text":"You see, you can take out\none or two hub trees,"},{"time":818080,"text":"but there comes a tipping point,"},{"time":820920,"text":"because hub trees are not\nunlike rivets in an airplane."},{"time":823880,"text":"You can take out one or two\nand the plane still flies,"},{"time":827440,"text":"but you take out one too many,"},{"time":829040,"text":"or maybe that one holding on the wings,"},{"time":831680,"text":"and the whole system collapses."}]},{"cues":[{"time":835000,"text":"So now how are you thinking\nabout forests? Differently?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":837920,"text":"(Audience) Yes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":839160,"text":"Cool."},{"time":841040,"text":"I'm glad."}]},{"cues":[{"time":842920,"text":"So, remember I said earlier\nthat I hoped that my research,"},{"time":846800,"text":"my discoveries would change\nthe way we practice forestry."},{"time":850200,"text":"Well, I want to take a check on that\n30 years later here in western Canada."}]},{"cues":[{"time":862840,"text":"This is about 100 kilometers\nto the west of us,"},{"time":865400,"text":"just on the border of Banff National Park."},{"time":869120,"text":"That's a lot of clear-cuts."},{"time":871020,"text":"It's not so pristine."},{"time":873980,"text":"In 2014, the World Resources Institute\nreported that Canada in the past decade"},{"time":879060,"text":"has had the highest forest disturbance\nrate of any country worldwide,"},{"time":883620,"text":"and I bet you thought it was Brazil."},{"time":887140,"text":"In Canada, it's 3.6 percent per year."},{"time":890700,"text":"Now, by my estimation, that's about\nfour times the rate that is sustainable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":897100,"text":"Now, massive disturbance at this scale\nis known to affect hydrological cycles,"},{"time":901460,"text":"degrade wildlife habitat,"},{"time":903460,"text":"and emit greenhouse gases\nback into the atmosphere,"},{"time":906380,"text":"which creates more disturbance\nand more tree diebacks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":911300,"text":"Not only that, we're continuing\nto plant one or two species"},{"time":914300,"text":"and weed out the aspens and birches."},{"time":917260,"text":"These simplified forests lack complexity,"},{"time":919860,"text":"and they're really vulnerable\nto infections and bugs."},{"time":923300,"text":"And as climate changes,"},{"time":925220,"text":"this is creating a perfect storm"},{"time":929420,"text":"for extreme events, like the massive\nmountain pine beetle outbreak"},{"time":933020,"text":"that just swept across North America,"},{"time":935820,"text":"or that megafire in the last\ncouple months in Alberta."}]},{"cues":[{"time":940980,"text":"So I want to come back\nto my final question:"},{"time":944980,"text":"instead of weakening our forests,"},{"time":946780,"text":"how can we reinforce them\nand help them deal with climate change?"},{"time":951700,"text":"Well, you know, the great thing\nabout forests as complex systems"},{"time":955740,"text":"is they have enormous\ncapacity to self-heal."},{"time":959700,"text":"In our recent experiments,"},{"time":961140,"text":"we found with patch-cutting\nand retention of hub trees"},{"time":964620,"text":"and regeneration to a diversity\nof species and genes and genotypes"},{"time":968780,"text":"that these mycorrhizal networks,\nthey recover really rapidly."},{"time":973940,"text":"So with this in mind, I want to leave you\nwith four simple solutions."},{"time":978300,"text":"And we can't kid ourselves\nthat these are too complicated to act on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":983180,"text":"First, we all need\nto get out in the forest."},{"time":987500,"text":"We need to reestablish\nlocal involvement in our own forests."},{"time":992060,"text":"You see, most of our forests now"},{"time":993700,"text":"are managed using\na one-size-fits-all approach,"},{"time":996940,"text":"but good forest stewardship\nrequires knowledge of local conditions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1002420,"text":"Second, we need to save\nour old-growth forests."},{"time":1007020,"text":"These are the repositories of genes\nand mother trees and mycorrhizal networks."},{"time":1014620,"text":"So this means less cutting."},{"time":1016900,"text":"I don't mean no cutting, but less cutting."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1019980,"text":"And third, when we do cut,"},{"time":1022660,"text":"we need to save the legacies,"},{"time":1025180,"text":"the mother trees and networks,"},{"time":1026740,"text":"and the wood, the genes,"},{"time":1028900,"text":"so they can pass their wisdom\nonto the next generation of trees"},{"time":1032819,"text":"so they can withstand\nthe future stresses coming down the road."},{"time":1036620,"text":"We need to be conservationists."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1039819,"text":"And finally, fourthly and finally,"},{"time":1043340,"text":"we need to regenerate our forests\nwith a diversity of species"},{"time":1046820,"text":"and genotypes and structures"},{"time":1049060,"text":"by planting and allowing\nnatural regeneration."},{"time":1052620,"text":"We have to give Mother Nature\nthe tools she needs"},{"time":1055540,"text":"to use her intelligence to self-heal."},{"time":1059180,"text":"And we need to remember\nthat forests aren't just a bunch of trees"},{"time":1062260,"text":"competing with each other,"},{"time":1063540,"text":"they're supercooperators."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1066700,"text":"So back to Jigs."},{"time":1068380,"text":"Jigs's fall into the outhouse\nshowed me this other world,"},{"time":1072860,"text":"and it changed my view of forests."},{"time":1075580,"text":"I hope today to have changed\nhow you think about forests."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1078940,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1080220,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}